👉 Loop Control Instruction

Sometimes we want our progress to execute a few set of instructions over and over again.
For example : print 1 to 1000 , print multiplication table of 7 , etc.

Loops made it easy for us to tell the computer that a given set of instructions need to be executed repeatedly.

👉 Types of Loops : 

Practically there are three types of Loops in JAVA :

1. While loop
2. do-while loop
3. for loop 

We will look into these one by one 

👉 While loops

              While(boolean condition)
              {
                  // Statement --> this keeps executing as long as the condition is true.
              }
If the condition never becomes false, the while loop keeps getting executed. Such a loop is known as an infinte loop.

